    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e583493f_8f7a4cb0",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-22T13:57:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are we assuming no grand-parents or more distant ancestors?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 202,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5f31c9a9_a0b1d0d2",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:28:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We are enumerating keys and in this mode every key can have at most one parent. \nWe group the keys by that parent because updating/deleting keys with ancestors automatically are done in a transaction over the whole entity group.\nIf done differently we get contention issues. \nI might misunderstand the question.",
      "parentUuid": "e583493f_8f7a4cb0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 202,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "80339956_2e4d459f",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:51:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Suppose my entity group consists of three kinds: Grandparent, Parent, Child. Child\u0027s key.Parent points to Parent; Parent\u0027s key.Parent points to Grandparent. Grandparent is the root of the entity group. Will it cause problems to group Child entities for the same Parent, but process Child entities for the same Grandparent in separate transactions?",
      "parentUuid": "5f31c9a9_a0b1d0d2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 202,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "951756bd_39fd9d4b",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-27T14:25:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This tool is lower level than that, it operates at the entity level. In many cases where you have ancestors you will have different Kinds of entities. We are only looping over one Kind at all times. The two operations we have implemented right now are primitive, but should not cause any problems with ancestors. If there are grandparents and the keys are not ordered by (parent, key) it will become inefficient, but not wrong. We should deal with it then.\nI am hoping we won\u0027t need these too often, they are more designed to deal with problems like I have right now where I indexed too much or I want to clean out a namespace.",
      "parentUuid": "80339956_2e4d459f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 202,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "612935b4_735df167",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-22T13:57:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This potentially overwrites a non-empty procSlice if we have one or more with-parent keys followed by a no-parent key that causes byParent[0] to reach maxSliceSize.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 231,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae7efb56_de7b9b78",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:28:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done\nMade it mutually exclusive, in practice that\u0027s unlikely, because one Kind usually has or doesn\u0027t have a parent across all entities.",
      "parentUuid": "612935b4_735df167",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 231,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "928dadde_1619655f",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T14:51:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The new code introduces a new problem. In the same situation, you will now never process byParent[0], because len(byParent[0]) \u003d\u003d maxSliceSize will not be true on later iterations.\n\nMaybe it would be better to fail early if we see entities both with and without a parent.",
      "parentUuid": "ae7efb56_de7b9b78",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 231,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "817a1ffb_6f64397d",
        "filename": "cmd/dstool/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-27T14:25:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes it will. The strategy here is as follows:\n- take one key and add it to the list of children with the same parent (if there is not parent \n  the key ID is 0) \n\n- check whether the parent key has changed (the keys come sorted by (parent/key)), if so send all keys for the old parent to be processed\n\n- if no such change in key parent occured check if the our parentless keys have reached the limit. If so process them. \n\nAfter the main loop there is another iteration through map of parents that will process any keys that have not been processed because of the above conditions. \n\nI believe this will work for all possible sequences of keys.",
      "parentUuid": "928dadde_1619655f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 231,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "07cdc367152c8e6ee35d4ed8b0f75b09d93b3a49",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
